artists.biography: Stiff Little Fingers are a punk rock band from Belfast, Northern Ireland. They formed in 1977, at the height of the Troubles. They started out as a schoolboy band called Highway Star (named after the Deep Purple song), doing rock covers, until they discovered punk. They split up after six years and four albums, although they reformed five years later, in 1987. Despite major personnel changes, they are still touring and recording as of 2011. Jake Burns, their lead singer, is the only member to have been with the band during all its incarnations, but in March 2006, original bass guitarist Ali McMordie rejoined them following the departure of The Jam bass player Bruce Foxton after fifteen years.

track.name: You Can't Say Crap on the Radio

wiki.content: While everyone els was having the "so called" british punk movment which was largely fronted by "THE VASTLY OVERRATTED" THE CLASH forced on them by a VERY helpfull BBC looking for a lost connection to the youth culture of the day. A young disgrunteld. rebellious band from Ireland calling themselves STIFF LTTLE FINGERS found the Learend ear of Dj "john Peale" who championed the real VOICE OF A GENERATION. with their heavy electric lead guitar that was screaming a melody to the under class, downtrodden teens of the day, AND giving a straight up, two fingered salute to the estabilishment. .DONT be fooled by what you read, or by the quaint old dated videos that get wheeled out on TOTP2 this music is STILL as valid today as it was THEN just catch the lyrics from TALK BACK Read more on Last.fm.
